                <h2>Rotation</h2>
                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Activate Arbiter of Justice</strong> -- Transform immediately and keep this active permanently. Wing Strikes passively apply Judgement to nearby enemies, seeding marks even when your other skills are on cooldown.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Spear of the Heavens</strong> -- Cast when available. This is your primary damage skill and Judgement mark applicator. Each hit marks every enemy in its area, setting up the chain reaction.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Blessed Hammer while moving</strong> -- Cast between packs or during SotH cooldown. Judicator Oath causes Blessed Hammer to detonate all active Judgement marks early for amplified damage, triggering the chain.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Maintain Auras</strong> -- Keep both Fanaticism Aura (Crit + Attack Speed) and Defiance Aura (Armor + Resistances + Unstoppable) active at all times. These are your permanent offensive and defensive buffers.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Judgement Day spreads marks</strong> -- The Judgement Day passive causes detonating marks to spread to nearby unmarked enemies. Combined with Seal of the Second Trumpet chains, this creates screen-wide cascading explosions.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Golden Hour feedback loop</strong> -- Aspect of the Golden Hour triggers additional Judgement marks from chain detonations. Each wave of explosions seeds the next wave, creating exponential damage scaling in dense packs.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Enhanced SotH cooldown reset</strong> -- Each Judgement detonation reduces Spear of the Heavens' cooldown. In dense packs, the chain reactions reduce SotH cooldown to near-zero, allowing constant recasting.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Critical mass -- self-perpetuating chains</strong> -- At sufficient density and CDR, the loop becomes self-sustaining: SotH marks &rarr; Blessed Hammer detonates &rarr; chains spread &rarr; Golden Hour re-marks &rarr; SotH resets &rarr; repeat. Your job is just to keep moving into packs.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Gameplay Tips</h2>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Arbiter of Justice is non-negotiable.</strong>
                    <p>If the transformation drops off, you lose passive Judgement application from Wing Strikes. This creates gaps in your chain reactions. Reactivate immediately if it expires.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>CDR thresholds matter more than raw damage.</strong>
                    <p>The build's power scales exponentially with Cooldown Reduction because faster SotH recasts mean more marks, more detonations, and more resets. Prioritize CDR on gear until the chain loop feels smooth.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Blessed Hammer is your detonator, not your damage skill.</strong>
                    <p>Do not invest heavily in Blessed Hammer damage. Its role is purely to trigger Judicator Oath detonations. The damage comes from the Judgement explosions themselves, scaled by your holy damage and Judgement-specific bonuses.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Boss fights require patience.</strong>
                    <p>Without add density, chain reactions are limited. Against solo bosses, focus on applying marks with SotH and Arbiter Wing Strikes, then detonate with Blessed Hammer. The damage is still strong but lacks the exponential AoE scaling of pack fights.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Seal of the Second Trumpet is the power spike.</strong>
                    <p>The build works without it -- Judicator Oath alone provides a solid foundation. But the Seal of the Second Trumpet ring transforms the build from "good" to "S-Tier" by enabling the chain detonation mechanic that defines this playstyle.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Position for density.</strong>
                    <p>In the Pit and Nightmare Dungeons, group enemies tightly before unloading SotH. The more targets marked, the more devastating the chain reaction. Use Falling Star to reposition into the center of packs for maximum mark coverage.</p>
